<div class="prose">

<p>Five real-world scenarios modeled on documented tectonic settings: <strong>Tōhoku</strong> (subduction megathrust), <strong>Anatolian / Istanbul</strong> (transform), <strong>Merapi</strong> (stratovolcano), <strong>Cascadia</strong> (subduction), and <strong>Hawaii</strong> (hotspot shield). Pick a scenario, spend a fixed budget on housing, hospitals, schools, and engineering technologies (base isolation, tsunami walls, early-warning systems, lahar diversion). Run the simulation — a real disaster strikes — and the data tells you which decisions saved lives.</p>

<div class="callout">
  <div class="callout-title">Sessions auto-log not yet live</div>
  Every attempt is scored on the spot, but the Sessions Sheet that would auto-log your attempts to your Google account isn't deployed yet. For now, <strong>screenshot your final score, grade, and budget used</strong> from the debrief into your engineering journal after each iteration. The auto-logging is on the way and will replace the manual step when it ships.
</div>

