<h2>Where this fits in the unit</h2>

<ul>
  <li><strong>Block 2</strong> — teacher-led Tōhoku demo. No student gameplay yet.</li>
  <li><strong>Block 4</strong> — first independent attempt (everyone on Tōhoku).</li>
  <li><strong>Blocks 6, 7, 9, 10</strong> — iterations on your chosen scenario for the <a href="/units/unit-3/assessment-engineering-portfolio/">Engineering Portfolio</a>.</li>
  <li><strong>Blocks 11–12</strong> — final defenses based on your iteration data.</li>
</ul>

<h2>Before your first run</h2>

<ul>
  <li>Have your <a href="/units/unit-3/assessment-hazard-profile/">Hazard Profile</a> open — you'll reference its boundary identification and dominant hazards in your engineering journal.</li>
  <li>Open your engineering journal (any format — typed, voice memo with auto-transcription, paired). Predict <em>before</em> you run, reflect <em>after</em>.</li>
  <li>Skim the <a href="/foundations/the-rubric/">rubric</a> — the Engineering Portfolio criteria are what your iteration evidence gets scored on.</li>
</ul>

</div>
